deck: Middle class family from Coast City related to earth's Green Lantern Hal Jordan.
description:
With a history of military background the Jordan family was originally composed by Martin and Jessica Jordan. They had three sons who would follow different paths after the tragic death of Martin.

Jack, the eldest son would married to Janice and had two sons: Jason and Helen (also know as Jennifer). Sadly all the family died in unspecific circumstances involving a supernatural force.

Hal, the second son would join the air force and eventually would join the intergalactic Green Lantern Corps. He is in an off-again-on-again relationship with Carol Ferris. In a possible future he could be parent of Jim Jordan.

Jim, the third son, married to Sue Jordan and had two sons: Howard and Jane. Having discovering the secret of his brother, he choose to stay in Coast City along with his family, taking the testimony of his father.

The Air Wave branch

The Green Lantern isn't the only heroic name associated to the Jordan family. Pre-Flashpoint, the name of Airwave was a heroic moniker used by a cousin of Martin, Larry Jordan and once by Larry's wife, Helen. The son of Larry, also called Hal Jordan, later would too become Air Wave. Post Flashpoint is unknown if the Air Wave branch of the family still exists.

deck: A race of crystalized aliens. They absorb other races by infecting them with crystals, which slowly turn others into Spherions themselves.
description:
The Calexi are a peaceful race, once living on the planet Malleon. One day, they were invaded by the Spherions. Initially, the Calexi thought the Spherions wanted their planet, but it turned out the Spherions wanted the Calexi themselves. The Calexi fled their planet and searched for a new world. But the Spherions chased them. Finally, one of the leaders of the Calaxi, Lumin, found a shell of a hollow world. Using the last of their resources and their advanced planetary-engineering, the Calexi built another world inside the shell, thus hiding from the Spherions.

But again, the Spherions found the Calexi. Not much later, Doctor Who and his assistent Josie Day arrived on Lumin's World. Josie quickly became infected too. But her partial crystalization, made her understand the language of the Spherions. She heard them talk, upon which the Doctor tried to communicate with them. The Spherions turned out to be a dying race in search of a new breeding ground. Josie asked the Spherions to trust the Doctor to find them a new home, which he did, thus saving the Calexi from extinction.
name: Spherions

deck: Deadpool's own team of mercenaries whom did 'heroic' work for the highest bidder.
description:
Origin

When the anti-hero known as Solo used the identity of Deadpool (and made it popular), it got Deadpool thinking to start his own team of Deadpool heroes. Hoping to increase his popularity, Deadpool gathered a group of questionable anti-heroes, among them Solo, Foolkiller, Slapstick, Terror Inc. and the true hero known as Stingray. At first the team was simply named "Heroes for Hire", but that was not agreed upon by the original founder of the Heroes for Hire, Luke Cage. It was then that the team switched names to "The Mercs for Money".

Creation

The Mercs for Money first appeared (although not named) in Deadpool Vol.4 issue 1 (2016).

Major Story Arcs

The Mercs for Money

After the team changed it names, it continued to do missions for money. Some of them where quiestionable. Especially the one when they where tasked to bring in a young mutant girl codnamed Negasonic Teenage Warhead. They where told that she was brought in to help her, but actually she was used in experiments. This and other problems caused extreme tension in the group. Eventually, the original group disbannded and left Deadpool to try and rectify their last mission all by himself. He went to the facility where he dropped of Negasonic Teenage Warhead and tried to free her. He was easily bested and thrown out of the facility, but then found a new group of heroes whom turned out to be the new Mercs for Money.

deck: A tortured and physiologically twisted family that lived inside the Decaster House. Due to their fragile mental state they resorted to cannibalism and all died within the confines of their home; eventually becoming evil spirits that haunt any who enter.
description:
Origin

The Decaster Family lived inside of a large manor known as the Decaster House and were led by Lionel Decaster. Lionel forced his wife and children to stay inside the house and never allowed them to leave, making them prisoners within their own home. Eventually the group began to reproduce more members of the family, resulting in deformed children due to the constant inbreeding. The conditions within the house and the mental state of it's inhabitants finally caused one of the Decasters to snap, this resulted in the death of Lionel Decaster at the hands of his granddaughter.

Unfortunately, this was not the end to their suffering. Due to their conditioning over the past several years the family never left the house, even when their food supplies began running low. Instead of finding food elsewhere they resulted to cannibalism and started killing one another off until the final Decaster died inside the home.

The Decaster's continued to live in their home, this time as tortured spirits who haunted any who entered their property.

Creation

The Decaster Family was created by Eric Powell for The Goon Color Special.

Team Evolution

While many of the Decaster's are left unnamed their roster consists of Lionel Decaster and 9 other Decaster family members.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Color Special

The Decaster Family decided to haunt The Goon and Franky when they entered the Decaster House in search of hidden treasure. Unfortunately for the Decaster Family, The Goon had been given a magical artifact that allowed him to physically harm spirits/ghosts, which resulted in the death of the family.
name: Decaster Family

deck: A duo of sack-wearing children fathered by Houstus Grave. They aid their father Houstus in digging up corpses to deliver to the Zombie Priest as members of his undead army.
description:
Origin

The Mongoloid Twins are the children of Houstus Grave and Mary Grave. They were born with odd deformities due to Houstus obtaining a rare leprosy after digging up corpses, which he then passed to Mary. Due to their horrific appearance they are forced to wear sacks on their heads, their true faces having never been seen. They now aid their father in digging up corpses for the Zombie Priest.

Creation

The Mongoloid Twins were created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

The Mongoloid Twins are seen early on in the series alongside their father, Houstus, engaging in a battle against The Goon and Franky. This battle eventually leads them to the Hobo Jungle where they're captured by the cannibalistic hobos. Thankfully they are able to speak "Hobo" and request to be let free, a request that is then granted by the King Hobo. Unfortunately for them, they're constantly defeated by the Goon and Franky, resulting in their abandonment of the Zombie Priest's cause and their departure from Lonely Street.
name: Mongoloid Twins

deck: The natives of the world of Imsk have the natural genetic ability to shrink in size, some even to microscopic sizes. Among their most famous members is the Legionnaire Shrinking Violet.
description:
Creation

The Imskians first appeared in the pages of Superboy and the Legion of Super-Heroes #234, (December, 1977).

History

Imskians are the inhabitants of the planet Imsk located in the Milky Way. The planets special attribute to shrink has since made its residents to have the ability to shrink.Their race didn't originate on Imsk, but were descendants of a Krill Colony. They arrived on Imsk almost a million years ago. Imskians are members of the United Planets in the 31st century.

There have been a few members of the race of Imskians who have special notoriety. The member of the Legion of Superheros, Shrinking Violet is one and the most famed. Although born on Earth her parents returned to Imsk and she was raced there. Another is Micro Lad who had at one time been rejected from the Legion tryouts. He would soon become a criminal and joined both the Legion of Superheros and a separatist group on Imsk. The last briefly appeared on another Legion tryout in the Pre-Boot universe, Ion was however murdered by Micro (Micro Lad).
name: Imskians

deck: The Mud Brothers (sometimes Mudd) are two ogre-like brothers who aid The Goon when he needs some extra muscle.
description:
Origin

The Mud Brothers were first seen after they were hired by a mobster known as Salvatore to collect a debt for him. While they originally set out with this mission in mind, they were given a better deal by The Goon and decided to work alongside him and his pals, defending Lonely Street.

Creation

The Mud Brothers were created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Team Evolution

The Mud Brother's have a conflicting team name; considering sometimes they're called the Mud Brothers while other-times being dubbed the Mudd Brothers; it is unknown what the official title of the group is or why it is so often altered.

The team disbanded after the death of Bill Mudd; thus leaving Charlie Mudd as the only surviving member.

Major Story Arcs

Drawing On Your Nightmares

The first appearance of the Mud Brothers, they entered the Goon universe after being hired by Salvatore to collect a debt that was owed to him. They eventually turned against Salvatore after being given a better deal by the Goon.

The Goon Volume Three

Alongside the Goon and his other allies, the Mud Brothers helped defend Lonely Street from zombies and other supernatural creatures that belong to the army of the Zombie Priest. Unfortunately they were caught off guard after a former ally of the Goon, Merle, sold information to the Zombie Priest, the attack resulted in the near death of Charlie and the death of Bill.

deck: The Church of the Sheltering Hand is a cult formed by Tenfingers based in Chinatown, New York City.
description:
Origin

Founded by a mysterious man only known as Tenfingers the Church of the Sheltering Hand is a religious organization that offers salvation and power to the downtrodden. It is extremely popular among illegal immigrants that live in and around Chinatown, New York City where it's temple was founded. Although it is connected to various criminal activities such as extortion and even murder the Church has applied for federal recognition.

Membership

The majority of the church's congregation is made up of immigrants that Tenfingers promises to keep safe from deportation and unemployment in return for money and loyalty. To prove their loyalty Tenfingers will often ask a member for a gift of one of their own fingers which most give up gladly. The highest ranking members of the church are gifted with a fraction of Tenfingers power and an extra digit. Notable church members are:

- Tenfingers - Founder

- Blindspot - aka Samuel Chung

- Billy Li

- Nonefingers

- Onehand

- The Eights - Highest ranking among the disciples of Tenfingers. Members include the mother of Samuel Chung.
name: Church of the Sheltering Hand

deck: Golden Retrievals is a company that handles the impossible tasks of repossession of Mondo Obscura items (If the emperor is late with his payment, it's up to Golden Retrievals to Repossess the Death Star) They also act as process servers, security escorts and insurance investigators.
description:
Golden Retrievals was formed by retired Astro soldier Master sergeant Euripides Hanson and his good friend Golden, the retriever. Euripides (nicknamed 'Rip' and sometimes referred to as 'Bosco') was an administrator in headquarters who accidentally stumbled onto the secret files of the 'Gunsmith unit' and the War-hound project. After the War, Rip found that there was money to be made in recovery, both by governments and private institutions. Realizing that he couldn't do it all alone, he found veterans who had difficulty assimilating into civilian life. The first, was his partner, Golden, the golden retriever. Golden was a biologically enhanced dog who had telepathic/psychic abilities. As a scout for the Astro Rangers, he was a valuable asset, yet even he was met with apathetic disdain. Golden was able to read minds, which Rip used to persuade and modify his situations. Golden's true purpose was hidden, so everyone just believed him to be an ordinary dog.

Next was Gunther Smythe: one of the three surviving soldiers from the Gun-wolf unit. These individuals were augmented with bio-kinetic weapons and nano-tech, allowing them to form firearms/weaponry with their bodies. The bullets/ammo was composed of psychic energy. The bullet being as powerful as one's willpower.

Lastly was Ruby Rekjavik: the Triptych woman, who as an adult is a cryokinetic, As a tween who is an Empath and finally the prepubescent super being that switched control in lieu of her situation.

These two are the prime retrievers. Whenever something has to be repossessed (alien artifacts, giant robots, Deathstars, battle cruisers et cetera) due to non-payment, or salvaged (Destroyed Deathstars, Battle cruisers Alien Artifacts) or summons served to unruly sentients, Golden Retrievals are the ones to call.
name: Golden Retrievals
